South Africa name virtual reserve side
South Africa named a virtual reserve team for Tuesday's opening match of
their tour of Argentina, France and Wales against provincial side Rosario.
Rosario, 400km north west of Buenos Aires, is one of Argentina's rugby
hotbeds.
South Africa:
Russel Bennett; Andre Snyman, Dick Muir, Joe Gillingham, Justin Swart;
Franco Smith, Kevin Putt; Schutte Bekker, Wayne Fyvie, Fritz van
Heerden, Hannes Strydom, Krynauw Otto, Marius Hurter, Henry Tromp, Toks
van der Linde.
Replacements: Joggie Viljoen, Jeremy Thomson, Breyton Paulse, Chris
Rossouw, Gary Pagel, Theo Oosthuizen.
Rosario:
Esequiel Jurado; Roberto Dippe, Ricardo Molina, Federico Flook, Romero
Acuna; Leando Bouza, Rodrigo Crexell; Paulo Bouza, Jose Garcia, Nestor
Oviedo, Raul Perez, Diego Bossicovich, Gabriel Cespedes, Mario
Silvetti, Roberto Promanzio.
Referee: Gianni Morandin.
Kick-off: 2300 GMT.
